pdate the `.csproj` to reference it.\n\nFor MSTest v3:\n- Test timeout can be set via `[Timeout]` attribute, or via `.runsettings` under `<MSTest><TestTimeout>` \n\n\n- The assembly resolution setting with `useLoadContext=\"true\"` is actually the default behavior in MSTest v3, so I don't need to explicitly configure it. I'm creating a `.runsettings` file that sets the test timeout to 30 seconds and disables deployment since that's no longer needed. I'm creating the `.runsettings` file with the migrated configuration and updating the project file to reference it instead of the old `.testsettings`.","outputTokens":990},"id":"4d8ce2fc-6915-44f2-bfc5-0e997aa42588","timestamp":"2026-04-03T01:16:51.478Z","parentId":"1cd17414-2c7d-42fb-947a-16569c4927b9"}
